
thon --> pattern to macth on
grep thon /usr/share/dict/words

# match regardles of case
grep -i thon /usr/share/dict/words

Reserved characters
. |--> a dot matches any character
    grep l.rts /usr/share/dict/words
^ |--> the caret or circumflex indicates the beginning of line
    grep ^fruit /usr/share/dict/words
$ |--> the dollar sign indicates the end of line
    grep cat$ /usr/share/dict/words


Character classes are written inside square brackets and let us list the characters we want to match inside of those brackets    

Capturing groups
Portions of the pattern that are enclosed in parentheses